    <div class="wp-block-qubely-accordion-item qubely-block-0ff295"><div class="qubely-accordion-item qubely-type-fill qubely-accordion-active"><div class="qubely-accordion-panel qubely-icon-position-right"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler" role="button"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler-label">What does IOU stand for?</span><span class="qubely-accordion-icon fa fa-plus"></span></span></div><div class="qubely-accordion-body" style="display:block"><div itemprop="text"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
                    <p><strong>International Open University</strong></p>
                    <!-- /wp:paragraph -->

                    <!-- wp:paragraph -->
                    <p>IOU is an online education provider that offers online courses from top universities, individual instructors, and companies around the world.</p>
                    <!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div></div></div>
    <!-- /wp:qubely/accordion-item -->

    <!-- wp:qubely/accordion-item {"uniqueId":"6dba99","itemNumber":1,"heading":"How can I enroll in a course?","defaultText":"Create stylish call-to-action buttons with Qubely Buttons. Play around with typography, design, border and more. Add animations and personalize it to engage visitors instantly.","panelColor":"var(\u002d\u002dqubely-color-3)","panelBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(254,241,243,0.75)","gradient":{"color1":"#EEEEEE","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"panelBgActive":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"#fc8ba1","gradient":{"color1":"#2476CA","color2":"#1A5FA4","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"typography":{"openTypography":false},"panelBorderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":"3"},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"bodyBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(239,239,239,0.18)","gradient":{"color1":"#f2f2f2","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"borderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":""},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"spacing":{"md":"25","unit":"px"}} -->
    <div class="wp-block-qubely-accordion-item qubely-block-6dba99"><div class="qubely-accordion-item qubely-type-fill false"><div class="qubely-accordion-panel qubely-icon-position-right"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler" role="button"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler-label">How can I enroll in a course?</span><span class="qubely-accordion-icon fa fa-plus"></span></span></div><div class="qubely-accordion-body"><div itemprop="text"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
                    <p>IOU courses are entirely on-demand. You can begin the course whenever you like, and there are no deadlines to complete it. IOU courses can be accessed from several different devices and platforms, including a desktop, laptop, and IOU mobile app.&nbsp;</p>
                    <!-- /wp:paragraph -->

                    <!-- wp:paragraph -->
                    <p>After you enroll in a course, you can access the course directly from the IOU platform. After login, click on the profile icon on the top right and select 'Enrolled Courses'. On this page, you will see all the courses that you have enrolled in. You can go to the course content page by clicking on the course name/featured image. Also, you will receive an email with the course link from IOU after you enroll in any course.</p>
                    <!-- /wp:paragraph -->

                    <!-- wp:image {"id":6579,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
                    <figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://iou.ac/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Screenshot-178-1024x368.png" alt="" class="wp-image-6579"/></figure>
                    <!-- /wp:image --></div></div></div></div>
    <!-- /wp:qubely/accordion-item -->

    <!-- wp:qubely/accordion-item {"uniqueId":"f92bb3","itemNumber":5,"heading":"Are courses on IOU free?","panelColor":"var(\u002d\u002dqubely-color-3)","panelBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(254,241,243,0.75)","gradient":{"color1":"#EEEEEE","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"panelBgActive":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"#fc8ba1","gradient":{"color1":"#2476CA","color2":"#1A5FA4","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"typography":{"openTypography":false},"panelBorderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":"3"},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"bodyBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(239,239,239,0.18)","gradient":{"color1":"#f2f2f2","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"borderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":""},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"spacing":{"md":"25","unit":"px"}} -->
    <div class="wp-block-qubely-accordion-item qubely-block-f92bb3"><div class="qubely-accordion-item qubely-type-fill false"><div class="qubely-accordion-panel qubely-icon-position-right"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler" role="button"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler-label">Are courses on IOU free?</span><span class="qubely-accordion-icon fa fa-plus"></span></span></div><div class="qubely-accordion-body"><div itemprop="text"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
                    <p>In IOU platform we have both free and paid coureses. Feel free explore the courses from <a href="https://iou.ac/courses/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">here</a>.</p>
                    <!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div></div></div>
    <!-- /wp:qubely/accordion-item -->

    <!-- wp:qubely/accordion-item {"uniqueId":"851e43","itemNumber":2,"heading":"Can I preview a course or lesson?","panelColor":"var(\u002d\u002dqubely-color-3)","panelBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(254,241,243,0.75)","gradient":{"color1":"#EEEEEE","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"panelBgActive":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"#fc8ba1","gradient":{"color1":"#2476CA","color2":"#1A5FA4","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"typography":{"openTypography":false},"panelBorderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":"3"},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"bodyBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(239,239,239,0.18)","gradient":{"color1":"#f2f2f2","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"borderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":""},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"spacing":{"md":"25","unit":"px"}} -->
    <div class="wp-block-qubely-accordion-item qubely-block-851e43"><div class="qubely-accordion-item qubely-type-fill false"><div class="qubely-accordion-panel qubely-icon-position-right"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler" role="button"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler-label">Can I preview a course or lesson?</span><span class="qubely-accordion-icon fa fa-plus"></span></span></div><div class="qubely-accordion-body"><div itemprop="text"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
                    <p>You can preview the introduction videos of every course which will give you an idea about what you will learn from the course. For free courses, you can access every video &amp; course content after you enroll in the course. For Paid courses, you need to pay the course enrollment fee through PayPal, and then you can access all the contents.</p>
                    <!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div></div></div>
    <!-- /wp:qubely/accordion-item -->

    <!-- wp:qubely/accordion-item {"uniqueId":"6407ab","itemNumber":3,"heading":"How long I can access the enrolled courses?","panelColor":"var(\u002d\u002dqubely-color-3)","panelBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(254,241,243,0.75)","gradient":{"color1":"#EEEEEE","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"panelBgActive":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"#fc8ba1","gradient":{"color1":"#2476CA","color2":"#1A5FA4","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"typography":{"openTypography":false},"panelBorderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":"3"},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"bodyBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(239,239,239,0.18)","gradient":{"color1":"#f2f2f2","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"borderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":""},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"spacing":{"md":"25","unit":"px"}} -->
    <div class="wp-block-qubely-accordion-item qubely-block-6407ab"><div class="qubely-accordion-item qubely-type-fill false"><div class="qubely-accordion-panel qubely-icon-position-right"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler" role="button"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler-label">How long I can access the enrolled courses?</span><span class="qubely-accordion-icon fa fa-plus"></span></span></div><div class="qubely-accordion-body"><div itemprop="text"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
                    <p>Once you're enrolled, you can start learning at any time. If you need to take a short break, you can come back and resume learning from where left. But you have to earn your certificate within 180 days.</p>
                    <!-- /wp:paragraph -->

                    <!-- wp:paragraph -->
                    <p>Please visit our learner’s Manual for more information like how to create an account, how to enroll in a course, and more. <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1wirRc7r9NkLmWnduL9WvHKIL1qhoh6km/preview" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Click to view</a></p>
                    <!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div></div></div>
    <!-- /wp:qubely/accordion-item -->

    <!-- wp:qubely/accordion-item {"uniqueId":"1a60df","itemNumber":5,"heading":"What happens if I don't complete an IOU course?","panelColor":"var(\u002d\u002dqubely-color-3)","panelBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(254,241,243,0.75)","gradient":{"color1":"#EEEEEE","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"panelBgActive":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"#fc8ba1","gradient":{"color1":"#2476CA","color2":"#1A5FA4","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"typography":{"openTypography":false},"panelBorderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":"3"},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"bodyBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(239,239,239,0.18)","gradient":{"color1":"#f2f2f2","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"borderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":""},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"spacing":{"md":"25","unit":"px"}} -->
    <div class="wp-block-qubely-accordion-item qubely-block-1a60df"><div class="qubely-accordion-item qubely-type-fill false"><div class="qubely-accordion-panel qubely-icon-position-right"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler" role="button"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler-label">What happens if I don't complete an IOU course?</span><span class="qubely-accordion-icon fa fa-plus"></span></span></div><div class="qubely-accordion-body"><div itemprop="text"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
                    <p>If you do not complete your course and earn a certificate within 180 days, your registration will expire and you will need to pay to re-enroll fee for paid courses.</p>
                    <!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div></div></div>
    <!-- /wp:qubely/accordion-item -->

    <!-- wp:qubely/accordion-item {"uniqueId":"ea45cb","itemNumber":4,"heading":"How can I pay for a course?","panelColor":"var(\u002d\u002dqubely-color-3)","panelBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(254,241,243,0.75)","gradient":{"color1":"#EEEEEE","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"panelBgActive":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"#fc8ba1","gradient":{"color1":"#2476CA","color2":"#1A5FA4","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"typography":{"openTypography":false},"panelBorderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":"3"},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"bodyBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(239,239,239,0.18)","gradient":{"color1":"#f2f2f2","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"borderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":""},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"spacing":{"md":"25","unit":"px"}} -->
    <div class="wp-block-qubely-accordion-item qubely-block-ea45cb"><div class="qubely-accordion-item qubely-type-fill false"><div class="qubely-accordion-panel qubely-icon-position-right"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler" role="button"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler-label">How can I pay for a course?</span><span class="qubely-accordion-icon fa fa-plus"></span></span></div><div class="qubely-accordion-body"><div itemprop="text"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
                    <p>Currently, IOU supports the Paypal gateway. So now the only way to make the payment via PayPal.</p>
                    <!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div></div></div>
    <!-- /wp:qubely/accordion-item -->

    <!-- wp:qubely/accordion-item {"uniqueId":"605312","itemNumber":5,"heading":"What happens if I fail course completion exam?","panelColor":"var(\u002d\u002dqubely-color-3)","panelBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(254,241,243,0.75)","gradient":{"color1":"#EEEEEE","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"panelBgActive":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"#fc8ba1","gradient":{"color1":"#2476CA","color2":"#1A5FA4","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"typography":{"openTypography":false},"panelBorderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":"3"},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"bodyBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(239,239,239,0.18)","gradient":{"color1":"#f2f2f2","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"borderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":""},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"spacing":{"md":"25","unit":"px"}} -->
    <div class="wp-block-qubely-accordion-item qubely-block-605312"><div class="qubely-accordion-item qubely-type-fill false"><div class="qubely-accordion-panel qubely-icon-position-right"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler" role="button"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler-label">What happens if I fail course completion exam?</span><span class="qubely-accordion-icon fa fa-plus"></span></span></div><div class="qubely-accordion-body"><div itemprop="text"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
                    <p>Most IOU courses have personalized schedules that begin when you enroll in a course. You have to accomplish a minimum of 80% marks on the course completion exam/quizzes to avail your certificate. In case you fail at the first attempt, you can retake the exam total 5 times.</p>
                    <!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div></div></div>
    <!-- /wp:qubely/accordion-item -->

    <!-- wp:qubely/accordion-item {"uniqueId":"173b6f","itemNumber":6,"heading":"Does the IOU certificate have any value?","panelColor":"var(\u002d\u002dqubely-color-3)","panelBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(254,241,243,0.75)","gradient":{"color1":"#EEEEEE","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"panelBgActive":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"#fc8ba1","gradient":{"color1":"#2476CA","color2":"#1A5FA4","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"typography":{"openTypography":false},"panelBorderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":"3"},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"bodyBg":{"openColor":1,"type":"color","color":"rgba(239,239,239,0.18)","gradient":{"color1":"#f2f2f2","color2":"#e5e5e5","direction":0,"start":0,"stop":100,"type":"linear"}},"borderRadius":{"radiusType":"global","global":{"md":""},"unit":"px","openBorderRadius":1},"spacing":{"md":"25","unit":"px"}} -->
    <div class="wp-block-qubely-accordion-item qubely-block-173b6f"><div class="qubely-accordion-item qubely-type-fill false"><div class="qubely-accordion-panel qubely-icon-position-right"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler" role="button"><span class="qubely-accordion-panel-handler-label">Does the IOU certificate have any value?</span><span class="qubely-accordion-icon fa fa-plus"></span></span></div><div class="qubely-accordion-body"><div itemprop="text"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
                    <p>According to IOU, “Verified Certificates ensure academic integrity" and definitly add values to your portfolio &amp; resume. To improve your skills &amp; learn from an online course, you have take responsibilities in your own hands to complete the course &amp; learn form it.</p>
                    <!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div></div></div>
    <!-- /wp:qubely/accordion-item -->

